attributes.Long form description: The student changes the controllers to a comfort grip, then to the joycon straps, then to handheld mode. The student stands with the Nintendo Switch. The student changes a game card and their micro SD card. The student turns on their Nintendo Switch, then turns it off.

attributes.Transcription: Now we're looking at the Nintendo Switch.
To start, please change the controllers from the screen to the joycon comfort grip.
To remove the controllers you can be pressed on the small round black button on the other side of the switch, and slide them out.

attributes.Action sentence: The student changes the controllers to a comfort grip.

attributes.Transcription: You should slide the controllers up on the left.
Great.
Now please change the controllers from the joycon comfort grip to the two joycons.

attributes.Action sentence: The student changes the controllers' grip from the comfort grip to the joycon straps.

attributes.Transcription: You should hold it the other way around so that the minus sign on the controller is matched with the minus sign on the joycon.
So it should look on the top of the controller, there is a minus and should be one as well on the top of...
Yeah, that's correct.
Please make sure both controllers are locked using the small white lock at the bottom.
Great.
Now please change the controllers from the two joycons to the handheld mode.
So back to the screen.

attributes.Action sentence: The student changes the joycon controller from the joycon strap to the handheld mode.

attributes.Transcription: Great.
Now please make the Nintendo stand.

attributes.Action sentence: The student stands with the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Transcription: Great
The next step is to change the game card.

attributes.Action sentence: The student changes a game card.

attributes.Transcription: It's the other way around.
Great.
Now please change the micro sd card.
The micro sd card is under the kickstand.

attributes.Action sentence: The student changes their micro SD card.

attributes.Transcription: Now please turn on the switch.

attributes.Action sentence: The student turns on their Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Transcription: Great.
Now please turn off the switch.

attributes.Action sentence: The student turns off their Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Transcription: To turn it off you should press it for at least three seconds and choose power options and power off.
Perfect.
Thank you it's over. You can press the stop button of the recording.
